## 5. SVG Implementation

A single Vue component using inline SVG. Each P&ID component is an SVG `<g>` group with reactive bindings:

```vue
<!-- BenchmarkSVG.vue -->
<template>
  <svg :width="canvasWidth" :height="canvasHeight"
       :viewBox="`0 0 ${canvasWidth} ${canvasHeight}`"
       style="background: #1A1A2E">

    <!-- Static connections -->
    <line v-for="conn in connections" :key="conn.id"
      :x1="conn.x1" :y1="conn.y1" :x2="conn.x2" :y2="conn.y2"
      stroke="#4A9EFF" stroke-width="2" />

    <!-- Components -->
    <g v-for="comp in components" :key="comp.id"
       :transform="`translate(${comp.x}, ${comp.y})`">

      <!-- Body -->
      <rect width="60" height="40" rx="4"
        :fill="getBodyColor(comp.id)" stroke="#4A9EFF" stroke-width="1" />

      <!-- Tag label (static) -->
      <text x="30" y="-5" text-anchor="middle"
        fill="#CCCCCC" font-size="10">{{ comp.tag }}</text>

      <!-- Live value (updates at 10Hz) -->
      <text x="30" y="24" text-anchor="middle"
        :fill="getValueColor(comp.id)" font-size="12" font-weight="bold">
        {{ getDisplayValue(comp.id) }}
      </text>

      <!-- Status dot -->
      <circle cx="52" cy="8" r="4"
        :fill="getStatusColor(comp.id)" />

      <!-- Ports (static) -->
      <rect x="-6" y="14" width="6" height="6" fill="#4A9EFF" />
      <rect x="60" y="14" width="6" height="6" fill="#4A9EFF" />
    </g>

    <!-- Alarm overlays -->
    <rect v-for="alarm in activeAlarms" :key="'alarm-' + alarm.id"
      :x="alarm.x - 4" :y="alarm.y - 4"
      :width="68" :height="48"
      fill="none" stroke="#FF3333" stroke-width="3"
      stroke-dasharray="8,4" rx="6" />
  </svg>
</template>
```

### Optimisation Variants to Test

- **SVG-A: Naive** — fully reactive, v-for with computed properties
- **SVG-B: Batched DOM** — bypass Vue, use `requestAnimationFrame` + direct `setAttribute` calls
- **SVG-C: Grouped updates** — use `document.createDocumentFragment` or batch DOM reads/writes

