## 6. Canvas (Konva) Implementation

Using vue-konva with the layered architecture:

```vue
<!-- BenchmarkKonva.vue -->
<template>
  <v-stage :config="{ width: canvasWidth, height: canvasHeight }">

    <!-- Layer 1: Static structure -->
    <v-layer ref="diagramLayer">
      <v-line v-for="conn in connections" :key="conn.id"
        :config="{ points: conn.points, stroke: '#4A9EFF', strokeWidth: 2 }" />

      <v-group v-for="comp in components" :key="comp.id"
        :config="{ x: comp.x, y: comp.y }">
        <v-rect :config="{ width: 60, height: 40, fill: '#16213E',
                            stroke: '#4A9EFF', strokeWidth: 1, cornerRadius: 4 }" />
        <v-text :config="{ x: 0, y: -15, width: 60, text: comp.tag,
                           align: 'center', fill: '#CCCCCC', fontSize: 10 }" />
        <v-rect :config="{ x: -6, y: 14, width: 6, height: 6, fill: '#4A9EFF' }" />
        <v-rect :config="{ x: 60, y: 14, width: 6, height: 6, fill: '#4A9EFF' }" />
      </v-group>
    </v-layer>

    <!-- Layer 2: Live data (listening disabled) -->
    <v-layer ref="dataLayer" :config="{ listening: false }">
      <!-- Populated imperatively, not via v-for -->
    </v-layer>

    <!-- Layer 3: Alarms (listening disabled) -->
    <v-layer ref="alarmLayer" :config="{ listening: false }">
    </v-layer>

  </v-stage>
</template>
```

### Optimisation Variants to Test

- **Canvas-A: Vue reactive** — v-for on data layer with reactive config bindings
- **Canvas-B: Direct Konva** — bypass vue-konva on data layer, create Konva.Text nodes imperatively, update via `node.text()` / `node.fill()`, call `batchDraw()` once per tick
- **Canvas-C: Layered + direct** — same as B but with separate alarm layer that redraws independently

