## 7. Measurements

### Metrics to Capture

For every test run, capture these per-frame metrics over a 60-second window (after a 5-second warmup):

| Metric | How to Measure | Target |
|--------|----------------|--------|
| **FPS** | `requestAnimationFrame` loop counting frames per second | ≥ 30 FPS sustained |
| **Frame time** | `performance.now()` delta between rAF callbacks | ≤ 33ms (p95) |
| **JS heap** | `performance.memory.usedJSHeapSize` (Chrome only) | No continuous growth (leak check) |
| **DOM node count** | `document.querySelectorAll('*').length` every 5 seconds | SVG: observe growth. Canvas: should be constant |
| **Alarm latency** | Timestamp when threshold value received vs timestamp when alarm visual painted (mark in rAF after update) | ≤ 50ms |
| **Long frames** | Count of frames exceeding 50ms | 0 in normal operation |
| **CPU usage** | Chrome DevTools Performance tab, percentage of time in scripting vs rendering vs painting | Observe distribution |

### FPS Measurement Code

Embed this in both implementations:

```typescript
// metrics.ts
class PerformanceMetrics {
  private frames: number[] = [];
  private lastTime = performance.now();
  private fpsHistory: number[] = [];
  private frameTimeHistory: number[] = [];
  private alarmLatencies: number[] = [];

  tick() {
    const now = performance.now();
    const delta = now - this.lastTime;
    this.lastTime = now;
    this.frameTimeHistory.push(delta);

    // FPS every second
    this.frames.push(now);
    this.frames = this.frames.filter(t => t > now - 1000);

    if (this.frameTimeHistory.length % 60 === 0) {
      this.fpsHistory.push(this.frames.length);
    }
  }

  recordAlarmLatency(wsReceiveTime: number) {
    // Call this in the next rAF after processing the alarm
    requestAnimationFrame(() => {
      const paintTime = performance.now();
      this.alarmLatencies.push(paintTime - wsReceiveTime);
    });
  }

  getReport() {
    const sorted = [...this.frameTimeHistory].sort((a, b) => a - b);
    return {
      avgFps: this.fpsHistory.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0) / this.fpsHistory.length,
      minFps: Math.min(...this.fpsHistory),
      p50FrameTime: sorted[Math.floor(sorted.length * 0.5)],
      p95FrameTime: sorted[Math.floor(sorted.length * 0.95)],
      p99FrameTime: sorted[Math.floor(sorted.length * 0.99)],
      maxFrameTime: sorted[sorted.length - 1],
      longFrames: sorted.filter(t => t > 50).length,
      avgAlarmLatency: this.alarmLatencies.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0) / this.alarmLatencies.length,
      p95AlarmLatency: [...this.alarmLatencies].sort((a, b) => a - b)[Math.floor(this.alarmLatencies.length * 0.95)],
      heapMB: (performance as any).memory?.usedJSHeapSize / 1024 / 1024,
      domNodes: document.querySelectorAll('*').length
    };
  }
}
```

### Alarm Latency Measurement

When processing incoming WebSocket data:

```typescript
ws.onmessage = (event) => {
  const receiveTime = performance.now();
  const readings = JSON.parse(event.data);

  for (const [id, reading] of Object.entries(readings)) {
    // Check threshold breach
    if (reading.value > 90 && previousValues.get(id) <= 90) {
      // This is a NEW alarm — measure latency
      updateAlarmVisual(id);
      metrics.recordAlarmLatency(receiveTime);
    }
    previousValues.set(id, reading.value);
  }

  updateAllValues(readings);
};
```

