## 8. Test Environment

### Hardware

Run on the actual target hardware (or equivalent) where the test bench software will be deployed. If not available, use a mid-range machine. Document exact specs:

- CPU model and clock speed
- RAM
- GPU (integrated or discrete)
- OS and version
- Browser/Electron version

### Browser Settings

- Chrome DevTools closed during measurement (DevTools impacts performance)
- No other tabs open
- Hardware acceleration enabled (default)
- Record one run with DevTools Performance tab open for flame graph analysis (separate from measurement runs)

### Run Protocol

For each scenario × each implementation variant:

1. Open the page, wait 5 seconds for warmup
2. Start WebSocket connection, begin receiving data
3. Let it run for 60 seconds
4. Capture metrics report
5. Run 3 times, take the median of each metric
6. Save Chrome Performance profile for one representative run

